namedLocations.description: Gujarat (/ˌɡʊdʒəˈrɑːt/, Gujarati: [ˈɡudʒəɾɑt] ) is a state on the western coast of India with a coastline of 1,600 km (990 mi) – most of which lies on the Kathiawar peninsula – and a population in excess of 60 million. It is the sixth largest Indian state by area and the ninth largest state by population. Gujarat is bordered by Rajasthan to the northeast, Daman and Diu to the south, Dadra and Nagar Haveli and Maharashtra to the southeast, Madhya Pradesh to the east, and the Arabian Sea and the Pakistani province of Sindh to the west. Its capital city is Gandhinagar, while its largest city is Ahmedabad. The Gujarati-speaking people of India are indigenous to the state. The economy of Gujarat is the fifth-largest state economy in India with ₹14.96 lakh crore (US$220 billion) in gross domestic product and a per capita GDP of ₹157,000 (US$2,300). Gujarat ranks fifteenth among Indian states in human development index.

namedPeople.description: Mishra or Misra is a Hindu Brahmin surname found mostly in the northern,eastern and central parts of India and Nepal. The density of Mishra is more among Saryupareen Brahmins, Kanyakubja Brahmins, utkala brahmin,Sakaldwipi Brahmins, Maithil Brahmins, Bhumihar Brahmins, Utkala Brahmins and Upadhaya Brahmins in Nepal. It is one of the most widespread Brahmin surnames in the fertile Gangetic plain region and in the Indian states of Delhi, Bihar, Uttar Pradesh, Odisha, Uttarakhand, Madhya Pradesh, Rajasthan, Assam, Hyderabad, and West Bengal. It is also found in countries such as Guyana and Trinidad and Tobago under the anglicized version of Misir, The surname is also found in Nepal, Fiji and Mauritius, as well as in other Indian diaspora communities. "Mishra" or Misra is similar to Maitreya or mapasa or Maitra or Maitri Mishra and both have same meaning. It is also found in countries such as Guyana and Trinidad and Tobago under the anglicized version of Misir, where many Mishras were taken to work on sugar plantations due to their agricultural prowess and skills in medical fields. The surname is also found in Fiji and Mauritius, as well as in other Indian diaspora communities.

transcript.text: Welcome to on Print shop.
In this video we will learn about code management.
Let's talk about key features and benefits.
Code allows your customers to share their requirement of placing an order with bulk quantity.
Different additional options are in a different timelines.
It helps you to manage all your code history in the admin.
Code can be converted directly into orders from back end as well.
After receiving the code request, you can easily perform actions on the code and even assign it to the printers etcetera.
All from the admin panel.
Let's have a look into the admin.
We go to view codes.
Here we can see all the codes received from your customers.
If you want to place a code from the back end, here's the button.
Just click on Add New code.
Here you can put the code title, put the first name, e-mail address, last name and enable this notify button to notify to the customer.
After entering all these details your code will be placed if customer places a code from the front.
Here you can see the code form.
So if the product is existing here, customer need to select from the drop down or if customer places a custom code here, they can put the details of the product.
So suppose if it's a business card quantity, let's say 100 details we can put over here and after adding all the details click on save and continue here.
You can see the code is placed when you put the details over here.
So this is the code has been generated successfully.
Now we go to the code section here we can see the details of the code.
Just click on add it.
So currently the code is showing quotation pending where we can see the product details given over here.
And here are the code actions which we need to perform whether we want to enter the code price post message to the customer or cancel the code.
And admin can put the comments over here and they can upload a sample job over here and then send it to the customer.
Here we need to put the price for 100 quantity.
Suppose it's 50 number of days, we can put two days and then click on save.
So here you can see it's changed to quotation now and when customer goes to their account.
So here they can see the details of the quotation, they can approve it or reject it and if they have approved they can put the comments and then they can approve the code.
So here we have an option where customer either can convert this code to the order from the front end or else we have an option from the back end.
If you refresh this page here you can see the quotation is approved now and here you have option to convert to the order directly from the admin.
So if you click on here, it will ask you to check the product and then click on continue.
So once you click on continue and click on OK, the order will be placed.
So here it will ask you to enter the shipping and billing details and click on confirm order.
So here the new order is placed successfully.

So in this way we can create a quotation into the order and here also we have option or if you have a printer to whom you want to send the quotation you can share the quotation to the printer by assigning them and after the printer approves the quotation then the code can be proceed in the same manner.
So for that here we can see there are certain quotations are there which are assigned to the printer.
So this here we can put the comment and and save and after that when you see here when the printer approves the code then it will be showing over here.
Thanks for watching this video.
In case of any further queries, feel free to connect with us.
Thank you.
